Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
set_global_always_keep(25.10)                    set_global_always_keep(25.10)

Name
       set_global_always_keep  -  Saves  the  specified  UDM  variable  to the
       .global file

Syntax
        set_global_always_keep

       [-help]

       variableName

       Saves the specified UDM variable to the .global file.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each set_global_always_keep parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man set_global_always_keep

       <variableName>
              Specifies the variable name.

              Data_type: string, required

Example
       The following command will save the UDM variable  timing_disable_inter-
       nal_inout_cell_paths with the value saved by the user:

       > set_global_always_keep timing_disable_internal_inout_cell_paths

       Then,  after  saveDesign,  the  following  line  will appear the in the
       .global file:

       set_global timing_disable_internal_inout_cell_paths true

Related Information
